On the surface, it looks like your "run-of-the-mill" Brooklyn pizzeria. In actuality, they're producing really tasty food at a level better than diner food. They don't fit the niche they appear to compete with and that's a good thing. Ignore the facilities and the covid safety setup.  Their Mexican food is fantastic. Their tostadas, tacos, quesedillas etc. are great. Actually, I think the chicken quesedilla is the best I've ever had. If all you want is a quality pizza or burger, you'll be good to go with their iterations. There are a few "👑" fried places nearby but leave those spots for your late night cravings, when everything is closed.

Tony's Pizzeria is great for pizza and if that's not your cup of tea; other foods such as nachos or gyros. Their menu is full of great options, ranging from tacos, spicy chicken legs, beef patties, and burgers. Drink options include bottled water, Arizona's, and various sodas including a Peruvian favorite, Inca Kola. Staff is also very friendly and inviting, and should never let you down. If you want a quick bite to eat, or a time to dine with friends while watching the Latin American soccer/football game, then this place is for you.
